At least 16 people have been injured after the taxi they were travelling in rolled on the R59 near the Swartkoppies Road in Alberton on Tuesday morning. On arrival, paramedics found the taxi in the centre median and occupants were found lying outside the vehicle. “Paramedics found that two had sustained critical injuries while 14 others had sustained minor to moderate injuries. Fortunately, no fatalities were found at the scene,” ER24 said. Two critically injured patients were transported to Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital while the remaining patients were transported to various provincial hospitals. Local authorities are investigating the incident. -TNA Reporter